      "id": "PopularPost242298",
      "post_content": "I can see your point OmegaSerris, at first glance, it may seem inferior to the other swords like [Sword of Fire and Ice](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sword of Fire and Ice). Its abilities may seem irrelevant or underpowered in constructed. But in the Legacy format, when you're running [Dark Confidants](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Dark Confidants) and [Bitterblossoms](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Bitterblossoms), having life gain effects without clogging important slots in your deck is important.  \nSlapping this onto a [Vampire Nighthawk](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Vampire Nighthawk) puts your opponent on a serious clock.  \nTry looking up the deck \"THE GATE\"..  \nAnd don't worry about getting flak, I respect people's opinion enough not to give them that.  \n  \nPlease pardon my English, I'm not a native speaker.  \n  \nThanks.  ",
      "posted_by": "zenitramleirdag",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost242298\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_post\">I can see your point OmegaSerris, at first glance, it may seem inferior to the other swords like <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Sword of Fire and Ice\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sword of Fire and Ice\">Sword of Fire and Ice</a>. Its abilities may seem irrelevant or underpowered in constructed. But in the Legacy format, when you're running <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Dark Confidants\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Dark Confidants\">Dark Confidants</a> and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Bitterblossoms\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Bitterblossoms\">Bitterblossoms</a>, having life gain effects without clogging important slots in your deck is important.<br/>Slapping this onto a <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Vampire Nighthawk\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Vampire Nighthawk\">Vampire Nighthawk</a> puts your opponent on a serious clock.<br/>Try looking up the deck \"THE GATE\"..<br/>And don't worry about getting flak, I respect people's opinion enough not to give them that.<br/><br/>Please pardon my English, I'm not a native speaker.<br/><br/>Thanks.<br/></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '242298'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                       