      "post_content": "I know I'll catch flak for this, but I think this is the weakest of the sword cycle. I'm not saying it's bad, though. The Pro-![White or Black](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=WB&type=symbol) and +2 toughness make most creatures only susceptible to bounce. Troll Shroud (Not Hexproof >.<) could do the same thing, but this route gives both a power boost and unblock-ability in some cases.   \n  \nSo all the swords are more or less equal up to this point. The abilities are what underwhelm me. Yeah, revival is nice. But we already established that this thing protects from most removal. So if you are playing this card correctly, your graveyard will be empty most of the time. Next is the lifegain. It has been pretty widely established that lifegain is negligible in most constructed cases, especially one-shots like spells and unreliable abilities (like this, you may not be able to get a hit in). You need something that takes advantage of it or you are just delaying the enviable.  \n  \nThe sword in the cycle from the same era, [Sword of Fire and Ice/au](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sword of Fire and Ice/au)... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "OmegaSerris",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost195966\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl08_post\">I know I'll catch flak for this, but I think this is the weakest of the sword cycle. I'm not saying it's bad, though. The Pro-<img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"White or Black\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=WB&amp;type=symbol\"/> and +2 toughness make most creatures only susceptible to bounce. Troll Shroud (Not Hexproof &gt;.&lt;) could do the same thing, but this route gives both a power boost and unblock-ability in some cases. <br/><br/>So all the swords are more or less equal up to this point. The abilities are what underwhelm me. Yeah, revival is nice. But we already established that this thing protects from most removal. So if you are playing this card correctly, your graveyard will be empty most of the time. Next is the lifegain. It has been pretty widely established that lifegain is negligible in most constructed cases, especially one-shots like spells and unreliable abilities (like this, you may not be able to get a hit in). You need something that takes advantage of it or you are just delaying the enviable.<br/><br/>The sword in the cycle from the same era, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Sword of Fire and Ice/au\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sword of Fire and Ice/au\">Sword of Fire and Ice/au</a>... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 195966)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl08_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl08_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '195966'); return false;\">\